      "type": "elementBody",
      "level": 2,
      "text": "The grid is often taught as a tool for order. It is more accurately understood as a system for generating productive constraint — a way of converting the blank page into a field of specific tensions. This paper traces grid thinking from Tschichold's asymmetric layouts through Müller-Brockmann's mathematical systems and into the responsive columns of contemporary screen design.",
